// AUTHENTICATION SYSTEM
//
// ⚠ CRITICAL — PRODUCTION REQUIREMENT ⚠
// These screens are fully built and production-ready in appearance.
// Before ANY real client data is stored, Supabase Auth MUST be
// connected. Without it:
// - Passwords are not hashed or stored securely
// - Sessions are not real
// - Data is not protected by row-level security
// - GDPR compliance cannot be guaranteed
//
// Supabase connection is a MANDATORY step before go-live.
// See: docs.supabase.com/guides/auth
//
// Screens built:
// 1. Landing page (marketing)
// 2. Sign in (email + password)
// 3. First-time account setup (set password from invite link)
// 4. Forgot password (request reset)
// 5. Password reset (set new password)
// 6. Account activation confirmation
// 7. Demo mode (role picker)
// ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// ── Authentication ───────────────────────────────────────────
// When REACT_APP_SUPABASE_URL + REACT_APP_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY are set:
//   → Real auth: supabase.auth.signInWithPassword({ email, password })
//   → Session:   supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange(...)  (wired in App shell)
//   → User data: fetched from users table after login
// When env vars are NOT set → demo mode (DEMO_ACCOUNTS below)

